@page "/Hero"

<h1>Welcome to World of Warcraft Information</h1>

<section class="info-section">
    <h2>What is World of Warcraft?</h2>
    <p class="paragraf">
        World of Warcraft (WoW) is a massive multiplayer online role-playing game (MMORPG) where you create a character and explore the fantasy world of Azeroth.
        Fight monsters, complete quests, join dungeons, and interact with thousands of players across the globe.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="info-section">
    <h2>A Look Into Azeroth</h2>
    <p class="paragraf">
        Azeroth is a vast world full of unique zones, each with their own creatures, factions, and stories.
        From the snowy peaks of Dun Morogh to the burning deserts of Tanaris – every region tells its own tale.
    </p>
    <img src="/images/map/azeroth.jpg" alt="Map of Azeroth" class="home-image" />
</section>

<section class="info-section">
    <h2>Choose Your Path: PvE or PvP</h2>
    <p class="paragraf">
        Are you a story-driven adventurer, or a fierce combatant against other players?
        In WoW, you can focus on PvE (dungeons, raids, quests) or PvP (battlegrounds, arenas).
        Many players enjoy both!
    </p>
</section>

<section class="info-section">
    <h2>Join a Community</h2>
    <p class="paragraf">
        Guilds are player-run communities where you can find friends, mentors, and teammates.
        Whether you're a raider, roleplayer, or casual explorer – there's a guild for you! U can also start your own guild with your friend and name it after whatever you may find is the most suitbale name for the guild! 
        You can also earn achivments with your guild through PVE and PVP content if u are doing it together with other memebers of the guild which can result in different kinds of rewards as gear, mounts or just gold!
    </p>
</section>